[center][size=6]🌿 Allellopathy[/size]

[i]Adds realistic allelopathy to farming. Nearby crops help or hinder each other through biochemical interactions, affecting growth speed, quality, and yield. Plan your farm layout wisely — companion planting matters![/i][/center]

[line]

[size=5]🧪 What is Allelopathy?[/size]

In real life, [b]allelopathy[/b] is a biological phenomenon where plants release biochemical compounds that influence the growth of neighboring plants — for better or worse. Some plants are natural companions that boost each other, while others are rivals that compete and suppress growth.

This mod brings that concept into Stardew Valley! Every crop you plant now interacts with its neighbors. Choose your farm layout wisely to maximize profits, or suffer the consequences of poor planning. 🌾

[line]

[size=5]✨ Features[/size]

[list]
[*]🌱 [b]Companion Planting System[/b] — Crops placed near each other can have positive or negative effects
[*]⚡ [b]Growth Speed Effects[/b] — Some combinations speed up or slow down growth phases
[*]⭐ [b]Quality Effects[/b] — Certain neighbors can apply, upgrade, or even remove fertilizer effects
[*]📦 [b]Yield Effects[/b] — Boost or reduce harvest cycles for regrowth crops
[*]💧 [b]Soil Effects[/b] — Some plants auto-water dry soil, while others dry it out
[*]💬 [b]Hover Tooltips[/b] — Hover over any crop to see if it's being affected by allelopathy
[*]✨ [b]Particle Effects[/b] — Occasional visual sparkles show positive and negative interactions
[*]🔔 [b]In-game Messages[/b] — Get notified when nearby crops interact
[*]⚙️ [b]Fully Configurable[/b] — Adjust effect strength, toggle messages, tooltips, and particles
[*]📋 [b]Generic Mod Config Menu Support[/b] — Configure everything from the in-game menu
[/list]

[line]

